The decision evaluates the constraints and metrics described in the system context and decisively recommends **Redis Streams** over Apache Kafka. 

The primary justification is that Redis is already in your stack, avoiding the high operational overhead and steep learning curve of Kafka for a small team without dedicated DevOps. Redis Streams easily handles your 10x throughput target (~5,000 req/s), supports consumer groups with retry semantics via the Pending Entries List (PEL), and allows for fast time-to-market within your 2-week constraint. Exactly-once semantics for billing will be handled via at-least-once delivery combined with idempotency keys in your existing PostgreSQL database, as no broker can truly guarantee exactly-once execution against external APIs.
